  "version": "5.0",
  "description": "This diagram illustrates the components of a Talos Linux cluster. Three main containers represent physical or logical boundaries: an Administrator workstation with CLI tools (kubectl, clusterctl, talosctl), a Control plane node running Kubernetes control components (kube-apiserver, etcd, kube-controller-manager, kube-scheduler) alongside Talos-specific daemons (machined, apid, trustd) and system services (udevd), and a Worker node running kubelet, containerd, kube-proxy plus Talos daemons. A Sidero Labs cloud container hosts the Omni management platform. Components connect via provides/requires interfaces shown as ball-and-socket connectors.",
  "imageDimensions": { "width": 1050, "height": 561 },
  "palette": [
    { "id": "k8s-blue", "hex": "#3333FF", "percentage": 25, "name": "Kubernetes Blue" },
